  "gitCommitMessage": "feat(mobile): preflight harness — 14-check verification before EAS submit\n\nRoot cause of APK#6 (aa769cc8) failure:\n  expo-router/babel plugin in babel.config.js — deprecated in SDK 50,\n  causes :app:createBundleReleaseJsAndAssets to fail at metro stage.\n\nFixes:\n- Remove deprecated 'expo-router/babel' from babel.config.js\n  (babel-preset-expo already includes it in SDK 50)\n\nNew: mobile/preflight.js (14 checks)\n  1. expo-doctor\n  2. tsc --noEmit\n  3. require()/import asset paths exist on disk\n  4. every package.json dep is in node_modules\n  5. every app.json plugin is an installed package\n  6. babel.config.js — no deprecated SDK 50 plugins, reanimated last\n  7. eas.json has preview profile\n  8. app.json schema (no newArchEnabled, package + bundleIdentifier set)\n  9. app.json + plugin asset paths exist on disk\n 10. metro bundle simulation (Linux only — Windows path bug)\n 11. expo install --check (native module versions)\n 12. package.json main entry resolves\n 13. .npmrc has legacy-peer-deps for EAS\n 14. babel transform smoke test — runs project's babel.config.js against\n     expo-router/entry to catch deprecated plugins WITHOUT metro\n     (this would have caught APK#6 locally)\n\nWired into package.json:\n- npm run preflight    (local)\n- eas-build-pre-install (runs on EAS server before npm install — aborts\n  build immediately if config is broken, no waste)\n\nCycle: run preflight -> fix top error -> repeat -> only submit when 0 errors.",
